        <h1>Who Needs to Submit CCR009? FCA Guide for Motor Dealers</h1>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">If your business is authorised by the FCA for certain consumer credit activities, you may be required to submit a <a href="/ccr009-return-assistance-motor-dealers">CCR009 return</a> through the FCA's RegData system.</p>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">For many FCA-authorised motor dealers, CCR009 forms part of their ongoing regulatory reporting obligations. The return allows the FCA to collect information about a firm's business model, regulated activities, revenue, marketing methods and staff involved in consumer credit activities.</p>
        <p class="ccr009-hero__lead">If your dealership introduces customers to finance, works with finance providers or carries out regulated credit broking activities, it is important to understand whether CCR009 applies to your business.</p>
